    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i just finished replacing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but now when i test drive it i get this really high pitched squealing noise when i hit the brakes. do u think its like a worn out sensor or maybe a stuck caliper?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Squealing brakes, especially after a job like replacing pads, is a common nuisance. It's usually not the sensor or the caliper itself being completely broken, though a poorly seated pad or some leftover grime can certainly cause a squeak. You'll want to check a few things, like making sure the new pads are seated perfectly flat against the rotor. Sometimes a little bit of rust or debris gets caught between the pad and the rotor, and that's where the noise starts.",
      "source": "target",
