    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk i checked the pads and they look seated right. the sound is like this super sharp, piercing screech every single time i press the pedal. it almost sounds unnatural... like a metal on metal sound but even higher pitch. could it be something inside the assembly that i missed?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A super sharp, piercing screech, like metal on metal but higher pitched, sounds like something is really grating, and that's a classic sign of something being misaligned or catching. You need to look *inside* the assembly, not just at the surface. Have you checked the caliper slide pins? Sometimes those pins get a bit sticky or haven't been lubricated properly, and when the caliper moves, it scrapes against the mounting bracket or the caliper body itself. It's a tiny thing, but a tiny thing can cause a big racket.",
      "source": "target",
